IZQUIERDA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"19","parent":"18","text":"Menor liberación de O2 a tejidos","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"20","parent":"13","text":"Mecanismo\\Ncelular directo","guid":"S-LmicbRn_ctGAp6jmJflA","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"Unión a citocromo oxidasa mitocondrial → bloqueo cadena respiratoria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"20","text":"Unión a mioglobina cardíaca → disfunción contráctil","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"20","text":"Generación de radicales libres (peroxidación lipídica)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"20","text":"Activación de óxido nítrico → vasodilatación, edema","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"25","parent":"13","text":"Cascada\\Ninflamatoria-\\Ninmunológica","guid":"HRD3DQ_dE0TDHJOX-VDz8w","children":[{"id":"26","parent":"25","text":"Peroxidación lipídica cerebral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"25","text":"Activación leucocitaria → adhesión endotelial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"25","text":"Desmielinización → base de SECUELAS NEUROLÓGICAS TARDÍAS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"25","text":"Apoptosis neuronal","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"30","parent":"13","text":"Órganos más vulnerables\\N(ALTO consumo O2)","guid":"M-yTyGCl9LCQLqAR68yYZw","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"CEREBRO → encefalopatía, edema cerebral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"30","text":"CORAZÓN → isquemia, arritmias, IAM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"30","text":"Feto → Hb fetal une CO con MAYOR afinidad que Hb materna","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"34","parent":"0","text":"Consideraciones\\NGeriátricas (AM)","guid":"D-P_MjWt3B4xsluACkiaQQ","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"MAYOR vulnerabilidad por\\Ncomorbilidades basales","guid":"3MMR53SLtBFiXM3pC820sA","children":[{"id":"36","parent":"35","text":"Cardiopatía isquémica previa → IAM con COHb >15%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"35","text":"EPOC/ICC → menor reserva cardiopulmonar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"35","text":"Anemia → menor capacidad de transporte O2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"35","text":"Deterioro cognitivo → dificulta reconocimiento síntomas","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"40","parent":"34","text":"PRESENTACIÓN\\NATÍPICA frecuente","guid":"53slub7QaeLVheLF1GrRmQ","children":[{"id":"41","parent":"40","text":"Síntomas confundidos con deterioro funcional habitual","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"40","text":"Cefalea atribuida a artrosis cervical","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"40","text":"Confusión/delirium atribuido a demencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"40","text":"Disnea atribuida a ICC o EPOC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"40","text":"Náuseas atribuidas a fármacos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"34","text":"Umbral de daño\\NMÁS BAJO","guid":"KXvn0MsuN99APlcLjYvWYg","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"COHb >15% ya es significativo con cardiopatía","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"46","text":"Muerte súbita descrita con COHb ~20% en ateroesclerosis severa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"49","parent":"34","text":"Exposición crónica subclínica\\N→ SUBDIAGNOSTICADA","guid":"8bzqhOVrLKeBJZUZVUOUqg","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"Cefalea recurrente invernal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"49","text":"Fatiga crónica inexplicada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"49","text":"Deterioro cognitivo progresivo atribuido a demencia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"53","parent":"34","text":"SESGO DIAGNÓSTICO\\Nen AM","guid":"wwSaiayeKAodVHDuRa86tg","children":[{"id":"54","parent":"53","text":"Secuelas tardías confundidas con deterioro propio de la edad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"53","text":"Seguimiento post-exposición inadecuado","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"56","parent":"0","text":"Manifestaciones\\NClínicas","guid":"brgGyUmCdCdiCwSuE9PRCg","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"Según nivel COHb\\N(orientativo, NO\\Ndefine gravedad)","guid":"9dTN5cdoFuZOub8dbTEMDA","children":[{"id":"58","parent":"57","text":"COHb <10% → cefalea leve, disnea de esfuerzo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"57","text":"COHb 10-20% → cefalea intensa, mareo, náuseas, vómitos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"57","text":"COHb 20-30% → confusión, taquicardia, dolor torácico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"57","text":"COHb 30-40% → alteración conciencia, síncope, arritmias","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"57","text":"COHb 40-50% → coma, convulsiones","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"57","text":"COHb >50% → FALLA MULTIORGÁNICA, MUERTE","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"64","parent":"56","text":"Correlación COHb-\\Nclínica es POBRE","guid":"kMPDlLX9t4MuPttqZJoe7Q","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"Niveles pueden ser normales al llegar a urgencias","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"64","text":"NO descartar intoxicación por COHb normal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"64","text":"Clínica y contexto > nivel de COHb","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"68","parent":"56","text":"Síntomas inespecíficos iniciales\\N→ MIMETIZA CUADRO GRIPAL","guid":"bM-hoZtJMni33dnkKYTbcg","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"Cefalea (síntoma más frecuente ~90%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"68","text":"Náuseas y vómitos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"68","text":"Mareo, debilidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"68","text":"Visión borrosa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"73","parent":"56","text":"Manifestaciones\\Ncardiovasculares","guid":"2JAW9J4orm4I-XS8gq2cvw","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"Taquicardia sinusal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"73","text":"Dolor torácico → isquemia miocárdica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"73","text":"Cambios ECG → depresión ST, inversión T, prolongación QTc","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"73","text":"IAM (NSTEMI > STEMI) → ~6% de pacientes con CO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"73","text":"Arritmias ventriculares","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"73","text":"ICC descompensada","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"80","parent":"56","text":"Manifestaciones\\Nneurológicas","guid":"gMuiIfq6IBOB7fL_kNAhDA","children":[{"id":"81","parent":"80","text":"Confusión, desorientación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"80","text":"Ataxia cerebelosa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"80","text":"Convulsiones","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"80","text":"Coma (GCS <8)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"80","text":"Edema cerebral","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"86","parent":"56","text":"Signo clásico: coloración rojo cereza\\N→ RARO y TARDÍO","guid":"_dO6cmwp-rOG93BNTyhg0A","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"Más frecuente en cadáveres que en vivos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"86","text":"NO esperar para diagnosticar","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"89","parent":"0","text":"Secuelas Neurológicas\\NTardías (DNS)","guid":"a8Mla8WaOgxCVuH7w3Dk2w","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"Aparecen 3-40 días post-exposición","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"89","text":"Incidencia 10-40% de sobrevivientes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"89","text":"MAYOR riesgo en AM, pérdida conciencia, exposición prolongada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"89","text":"Manifestaciones","guid":"","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"Deterioro cognitivo (memoria, atención, concentración)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"93","text":"Cambios personalidad, apatía","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"93","text":"Parkinsonismo secundario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"93","text":"Trastornos del ánimo (depresión, ansiedad)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"93","text":"Incontinencia urinaria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"93","text":"Síndrome disejecutivo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"100","parent":"89","text":"Neuroimagen","guid":"","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"TC → hipodensidad globo pálido bilateral (clásico)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"100","text":"RM → lesiones sustancia blanca periventricular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"100","text":"RM → desmielinización difusa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"104","parent":"89","text":"Seguimiento neuropsicológico recomendado hasta 6 semanas","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"SOSPECHA CLÍNICA\\N= CLAVE","guid":"cZBdc3uzevDdt3xspZP1uA","children":[{"id":"107","parent":"106","text":"Síntomas + contexto ambiental (invierno, calefacción, espacio cerrado)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"106","text":"Múltiples afectados simultáneos → ALTA sospecha","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"106","text":"Síntomas que mejoran al salir del ambiente","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"110","parent":"105","text":"Laboratorio","guid":"","children":[{"id":"111","parent":"110","text":"COHb en GASOMETRÍA ARTERIAL\\N→ gold standard","guid":"E_m-9OeIb6d4N5M1CxJmSA","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"Fumadores: basal 3-8%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"111","text":"No fumadores: basal <3%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"111","text":"Sintomático: generalmente >10%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"111","text":"Grave: >25%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"116","parent":"110","text":"Lactato → marcador de hipoxia tisular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"110","text":"Troponina → descartar isquemia miocárdica (OBLIGATORIO en AM)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"110","text":"Gases arteriales → acidosis metabólica, PaO2 normal (falso)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"119","parent":"105","text":"Pulsioximetría convencional\\N→ NO ÚTIL","guid":"F0dJFZARABLi5Wl_KUTdmg","children":[{"id":"120","parent":"119","text":"SpO2 FALSAMENTE NORMAL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"119","text":"COHb absorbe luz similar a oxiHb","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"119","text":"GAP SpO2-SaO2 = nivel de COHb","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"123","parent":"105","text":"CO-oximetría de pulso\\N→ screening rápido","guid":"VpIW0-L6vvp48csMA2omng","children":[{"id":"124","parent":"123","text":"ACEP 2017/2025: NO recomendada para diagnóstico (Nivel B)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"123","text":"Útil como screening prehospitalario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"123","text":"Puede subestimar COHb real","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"127","parent":"105","text":"ECG obligatorio","guid":"","children":[{"id":"128","parent":"127","text":"Cambios isquémicos (ST, T)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"127","text":"Arritmias","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"127","text":"Prolongación QTc","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"131","parent":"105","text":"Diagnósticos\\Ndiferenciales","guid":"eVvSlw4bxH8AdIcn2QExEw","children":[{"id":"132","parent":"131","text":"Síndrome gripal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"131","text":"Intoxicación alimentaria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"131","text":"Cefalea tensional/migraña","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"131","text":"ACV/AIT","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"131","text":"Delirium por otra causa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"131","text":"Intoxicación por cianuro (coexistente en incendios)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"138","parent":"0","text":"Tratamiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"139","parent":"138","text":"OXÍGENO AL 100%\\N= PIEDRA ANGULAR","guid":"rsawTVmNTfY8P7gAO26Mjw","children":[{"id":"140","parent":"139","text":"Mascarilla de no reinhalación (MNR) alto flujo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"139","text":"Vida media COHb en aire ambiente → ~320 min","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"139","text":"Vida media COHb con O2 100% NBO → ~80 min","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"139","text":"Vida media COHb con HBO 3 ATA → ~23 min","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"139","text":"Mantener hasta COHb <3% Y resolución síntomas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"139","text":"Mínimo 6 horas de oxigenoterapia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"146","parent":"138","text":"Oxígeno\\NHiperbárico\\N(HBO)","guid":"OLc3Cm9bsP-H7hWgjmpfIg","children":[{"id":"147","parent":"146","text":"ACEP 2025 →\\Nrecomendación NIVEL C\\N(evidencia Clase III)","guid":"9co6Ffi9jqpoOXL3_XHODA","children":[{"id":"148","parent":"147","text":"Puede beneficiar outcomes neurocognitivos tardíos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"147","text":"Particularmente mejoría en MEMORIA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"147","text":"NO mandatorio → decisión caso a caso","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"151","parent":"146","text":"Indicaciones\\Nsugeridas","guid":"WuoyR8E6Ph1nNglZufrJZw","children":[{"id":"152","parent":"151","text":"COHb >25% (>15% si cardiopatía o AM)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"151","text":"Pérdida de conciencia/síncope","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"154","parent":"151","text":"Síntomas neurológicos persistentes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"151","text":"Isquemia miocárdica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"151","text":"Acidosis metabólica severa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"151","text":"Síntomas persistentes tras 4h de NBO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"151","text":"EMBARAZADA → siempre indicado (independiente COHb)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"159","parent":"146","text":"Timing CRÍTICO →\\Nidealmente <6 horas\\Npost-exposición","guid":"GlEaQdL0LG92CzZx0WFj2A","children":[{"id":"160","parent":"159","text":"Beneficio disminuye con retraso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"159","text":"Transferencia a centro hiperbárico NO debe retrasar NBO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"159","text":"Riesgo de deterioro durante traslado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"163","parent":"146","text":"Controversia\\Nvigente","guid":"ley5wW7OWhtGq8uMWgAc_w","children":[{"id":"164","parent":"163","text":"Revisión Cochrane → sin reducción clara de secuelas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"163","text":"Solo evidencia Clase III disponible","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"163","text":"1 RCT positivo (Weaver 2002) vs estudios negativos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"163","text":"Hiperoxia puede ser deletérea (radicales libres)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"168","parent":"138","text":"Soporte\\Ngeneral","guid":"NvK2BQDcFXoLqeO8lIeqhA","children":[{"id":"169","parent":"168","text":"Monitorización cardíaca continua","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"168","text":"Manejo de arritmias","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"168","text":"Control de convulsiones (BZD)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"168","text":"Manejo de edema cerebral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"168","text":"Evaluación y tratamiento de isquemia miocárdica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"168","text":"Considerar intoxicación por CIANURO concomitante en incendios","guid":"","children":[{"id":"175","parent":"174","text":"Hidroxocobalamina 5g IV (antídoto CN)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"176","parent":"138","text":"Embarazada","guid":"","children":[{"id":"177","parent":"176","text":"HBO SIEMPRE indicada (independiente de COHb materno)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"176","text":"Hb fetal tiene MAYOR afinidad por CO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"176","text":"Feto actúa como sumidero de CO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"176","text":"Oxigenoterapia prolongada (eliminación fetal más lenta)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"181","parent":"0","text":"Prevención","guid":"","children":[{"id":"182","parent":"181","text":"Detectores de CO en hogares (OBLIGATORIOS en muchos países)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"181","text":"Mantención regular de calefactores y chimeneas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"181","text":"Ventilación adecuada de espacios con combustión","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"181","text":"NO usar generadores dentro de viviendas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"181","text":"NO usar braseros en espacios cerrados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"181","text":"Educación a población de riesgo (AM que viven solos)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"181","text":"Chile → contexto calefacción a leña/parafina en sur","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"189","parent":"0","text":"Perlas\\NClínicas","guid":"60OaEvjlCs5zMXGT7ih08w","children":[{"id":"190","parent":"189","text":"SpO2 NORMAL no descarta intoxicación por CO → solicitar COHb en gases","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"189","text":"AM con cardiopatía: umbral de daño más bajo → evaluar isquemia con COHb >15%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"189","text":"Síntomas gripales en invierno + espacio cerrado + calefacción = PENSAR EN CO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"189","text":"Múltiples pacientes del mismo domicilio con síntomas similares → CO hasta demostrar lo contrario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"189","text":"Secuelas neurológicas tardías pueden aparecer semanas después → seguimiento neuropsicológico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"189","text":"HBO no es mandatorio (ACEP 2025, Nivel C) → decisión individualizada según gravedad y disponibilidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"189","text":"En incendios siempre considerar intoxicación CONCOMITANTE por cianuro → hidroxocobalamina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"189","text":"Pulsioximetría convencional es INÚTIL → da valores falsamente normales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"198","parent":"189","text":"Correlación COHb-clínica es pobre → NO usar COHb como único criterio de gravedad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"189","text":"En AM el delirium por CO puede ser atribuido erróneamente a demencia → SESGO DIAGNÓSTICO","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"200","parent":"0","text":"VER\\NTAMBIÉN","guid":"E2RMa96p93yIxOJuVruEUg","children":[{"id":"201","parent":"200","text":"→ Delirium en Urgencias (Geriatría de Urgencias)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"202","parent":"200","text":"→ Presentación Atípica en AM (Geriatría de Urgencias)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"200","text":"→ Manejo Prehospitalario AM (Geriatría de Urgencias)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"200","text":"→ Valoración Geriátrica en Urgencias (Geriatría de Urgencias)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"205","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"zGWj9vWZs63Pn81KADpVAw","children":[{"id":"206","parent":"205","text":"1. ACEP Clinical Policies Subcommittee. A Critical Issue in the Management of Adult Patients Presenting to the ED With Acute CO Poisoning. Ann Emerg Med. 2025;85(4):e45-e59.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"207","parent":"205","text":"2. Hampson NB. Practice recommendations in the diagnosis, management, and prevention of carbon monoxide poisoning. Am J Respir Crit Care Med. 2012;186(11):1095-101.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"208","parent":"205","text":"3. Weaver LK et al. Hyperbaric oxygen for acute carbon monoxide poisoning. N Engl J Med. 2002;347(14):1057-67.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"205","text":"4. Rose JJ et al. Carbon monoxide poisoning: pathogenesis, management, and future directions of therapy. Am J Respir Crit Care Med. 2017;195(5):596-606.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"205","text":"5. Anand J et al. Management of acute intoxication with carbon monoxide. Int J Occup Med Environ Health. 2025;38(5):457-73.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"211","parent":"205","text":"6. Roderique JD et al. A modern literature review of carbon monoxide poisoning theories, therapies, and potential targets. Toxicology. 2015;334:45-58.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"212","parent":"205","text":"7. Guzman JA. Carbon monoxide poisoning. Crit Care Clin. 2012;28(4):537-48.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"213","parent":"205","text":"8. Al-Busaidi S et al. NSTEMI Following Acute CO Poisoning in an Elderly Female: A Case Report. J Oman Med Assoc. 2024;1(1):81-86.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"214","parent":"205","text":"9. Buckley NA et al. Hyperbaric oxygen for carbon monoxide poisoning. Cochrane Database Syst Rev. 2011;(4):CD002041.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"215","parent":"205","text":"10. Townsend CL, Maynard RL. Effects on health of prolonged exposure to low concentrations of carbon monoxide. Occup Environ Med. 2002;59(10):708-11.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":215,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"Intox CO iPad (1)","id":"map_794","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Intox CO iPad (1)"}